\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Something funny?\'a0\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 "This...stuff"?\'a0Oh. Okay. I see. You think this has nothing to do with you.\'a0You go to your closet and you select...I don't know...that lumpy blue sweater, for instance because you're trying to tell the world that you take yourself too seriously to care about what you put on your back.\'a0But what you don't know is that that sweater is not just blue.\'a0It's not turquoise. It's not lapis. It's actually cerulean.\'a0And you're also blithely unaware of the fact that in 2002, Oscar de la Renta did a collection of cerulean gowns.\'a0And then I think it was Yves Saint Laurent,\'ad wasn't it?\'ad Who showed cerulean military jackets.\'a0I think we need a jacket here.\'a0And then cerulean quickly showed up in the collections of eight different designers. And then it, uh, filtered down through the department stores and then trickled on down into some tragic Casual Corner where you, no doubt, fished it out of some clearancebin.\'a0However, that blue represents millions of dollars and countless jobs and it's sort of comical how you think that you've made a choice that exempts you from the fashion industry when, in fact you're wearing a sweater that was selected for you by the people in this room from a pile of stuff.\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Get me Isaac.\'a0I don't see my breakfast here. Are my eggs here? Where are my eggs?\'a0Pick up the Polaroids from the lingerie shoot.\'a0Have the brakes checked on my car.\'a0Where's that piece of paper I had in my hand yesterday morning?\'a0Pick up my shoes from Blahnik, and then go get Patricia.\'a0Get me that little table that I liked at that store on Madison.\'a0Get us a reservation for dinner tonight at that place that got the good review.\'a0Get me Isaac.\'a0Thirty-six thank-you notes delivered today.\'a0Where is everyone?\'a0Why is no one working?\'a0[
\fs28 Miranda's voice overlapping
\fs32 ]\'a0\cf2 \strokec2 \
